<br>
Do you just say &quot;Yeah, I died in so-and-so and I need to get my body&quot;?<br>
<br>
I've seen people referring to it as collecting their fake bodies, but I don't really like that route.<br>
<br>
This is an example of what I do. ...and probably will do cause I will be going to Sol A soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;A curse on all goblinkind, for they have slain my entourage travelling to the gnomes of the Solusek Mining Company!  I need must collect the dead now.  Bother me not!&quot;<br>
<br>
Sometimes I also say &quot;My fool of a lackey has gone and gotten himself killed again - I must retrieve his corpse, for he holds valuables of mine.&quot;<br>
<br>
Just wondering how some of the others on FV handle death and CR in character.<br>
<br>
Avalis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 5:43:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1076.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Death</span><hr size=1> Well, I'm fond of saying, &quot;I seem to have dropped my sword somewhere...&quot; and its usually received well by others, since they know what I mean (I AM naked, you know) and it doesn't disrupt RP really (A Loda Kai Brigand just killed me 3 times in a row!). <p>Shiden
